items.text: A serene neighbourhood food centre just outside city centre. Kind of a destination as it is situated near but not along major roads. Goreng Pisang is very good here. LE Bakery nearby also popular.
Xiang Xiang teh C is the best!
Xiang Xiang coffee stall #01-9
Chicken rice is the best here! Followed by the unique soya bean.
Sheng Sheng Fried Prawn Noodle isn't bad, worth a try!
Best chee cheong fun!! Made on the spot!
Good spice carrot cake! Slightly crispy which adds texture and chili has hint of belachan. Shiok!
Hokkien mee and peranakan kueh!
Albert St Fish Porridge and $2 prawn noodles are nice. So is the kuay chap porridge stall, very homecooked and not too oily
STALL:白桥海鲜汤小吃 Seafood soup with yam rice is a must-try.!^^ Cost S$4.00
Good spice carrot cake #01-20
Prawn mee!!!
Chicken rice. Prawn noodles. $2 fried rice. Wanton mee. All awesome.
Handmade chee cheong fun
Tan kee roaster is the best!
Great cabbage dish.
Ou yuan pork porridge also nice... Try the wan tan mee too!
GOOD SPICE CARROT CAKE is a must try!
Go for Cambridge Road HK Roast. The lady was very friendly, and the roast pork and char siew were great, topped with a good soup and veg all for $3. Super value for money.
Xin Heng Kee Chicken & Duck Rice, despite the long queue, has what I think 'value for $' + quality. Worth the wait. (Y)
Vadai (fried Indian donut) @ #01-08 is yummy, v light when it's just fried. Can't stop @ 1 :-)
Old Skool Wanton Mee by Soon Kee. Chilli paste is thick and spicy. Opt for black sauce for non-chilli lovers.
Watch out for cranky prawn noodle auntie who will give u commands and ask u to stand one corner!
Chee Cheong Fun is not bad :) It is fresh and made right after you order.
Nice duck rice
Kopi (local coffee): Remember d Soup Nazi in Seinfeld? Look 4 Kopi Nazi @ this mkt. New Fashion #01-39. His premium blended java brew is thick & generous. Premium, but still affordable prices too ;-)
👷: Singaporean chicken rice!
White Bee Hoon & Hokkien Prawn Noodles!
Cambridge Road Yong Tau Foo is the best ever! Nice aunty and uncle too!
Traditional Carrot Cake, visit Good Spice Carrot Cake. Cheap, Tasty & best of all, Generous eggs serving! A $3/- order comes w/4 eggs! Note: Long queue as it's a one old man team doing cook to order.
Roast pork hainan n prawn mie
品味 at #01-25 has giant chwee kueh! Chai poh is pretty good too - not too salty with a hint of sweetness.
Good traditional breakfast
Heaven here, cheap and nice food..
Love the pancake here ! Must try !
Don't sit outside. Too many pigeons flying around!
Food is cheap and good
Noya cakes and extra large chwee kuey yummy
Stall 01-48. Sell nice porridge and economic mix vege rice. Must try =)
The chicken rice here is the best in pek Kio and some say cambridge road!
Fresh Chee Cheong fun is a must try
Pek kio seafood delights stall serves yummy fish soup. Their yam rice are fragrant and the chap chai is delish!
Mi chiam kueh (Chinese pancake): Die die must q up & buy some @ Yean Heng Pancake #01-32. Go 4 their fresh grounded peanut filling
Roasted meat: Wonder wat d long q @ Xin Heng Kee Chicken & Duck Rice stall #01-14 is all abt? Fresh, succulent & value 4 money. Plus young couple owners v cheery lot :-)
Must try.. Johan Nasi Lemak....
Try the prawn noodles and chee cheong fan ! Favorite breakfast place
Dinner options limited. On a typical day, 10 stalls r open: 5 drinks stalls, & 5 food stalls (Indian, fried kuay teow/oysters, fried rice/hor fun, fish bee hoon, zi char) :-(
Prawn noodles #01-45 big fresh and clean prawns! Also nice soup with fresh garlic. Run by boss of #01-35 Seafood Delights so you know it's good! :D
$0.50 per cup of soya milk/chin chow at Min Hiang (#01-21)! Unbelievable!!!
Prawn noodles: 2 stalls 2 choose. Taukehs eat @ Wah Kee #01-15. Soup is thick & has a kick. The other #01-41 is run by young couple & comes w kangkong vege. U can ask 4 boiled pigskin, chilli powder
HerWorldPlus recommends: fish soup noodles fr Ng Seng Heng #46, Pin Wei Hong Kong Style Chee Cheong Fun #25, Wah Kee Big Prawn Noodles #15, hor fun fr Tong Siew Fried Rice #23
The prawn noodle soup from Wah Kee had a very strong garlic taste which I didn't like.
the hong kong style chee cheong fun is the best !
Old uncle Carrot Cake still taste good..  $1.50 is cheap..
Awesome chee cheong fun! Must try!! :)
Try the Char Siew or Prawn Chee Cheong Fun at #01-25
There's a SingPost postbox near the food centre. @ corner facing the pedestrian crossing. Mon-Thu 5pm collection. Fri 6pm. No mail collection on weekends
Like any other Hawker ...lots to choose from ...
Look nice but no tease
The legendary prawn mee is alright.. Must eat!!!
Try the nasi lemak!
A spacious, breezy and clean center in a suburban setting with lots of great food. Enjoyed the sliced fish soup, prawn mee and carrot cake. Will be coming back to sample more.
$2 fried rice is nice!
new fashion coffee stall - pricey, but worth every cent. You must try!
Wah kee Big Prawn noodles vendor attitude sucks.
Yummy fried rice & fried hor fun from this stall; and only $2.50 each! Cheap & good!
Honey lemon & lime drink: Thirst-quenching on a hot day. Stall #01-37. They also sell fresh sugar cane drink
Yong tau foo: There r 2 stalls but i go for stall #01-17. In last 2.5 decades I hv lived here, avoided d 2nd cos they look unhygienic (sorry!)
Pek Kio Seafood Delights - the fish soup here is really nice. The meat is firm and sweet. ;)
The 1 n only Bak chor mee is the best
lai hiang pork rip prawn mee
Try this zi char 01-43 looks yummy, fried fish head, prawn and sweet and sour pork.
One of the few places in sg where you can find $1.50 fried carrot cake. Try the freshly made Chee Cheong fan too.
#01-20 good spice carrot cake . Yummy
Kedongdong fruit juice. Savour this rare-in-S'pore drink @ #01-27. Also known as umbra (or ampulla in Penang) or balonglong, dis ice-cold, sour drink is gr8 on hot days!
Farrer park niang dou fu is good! ESP the fried mince ball! Cannot find elsewhere! I like everything here. The others outside are too commercial n all highly processed.
Old-school hawker with reasonable prices and good quality food.
Wan Kee Big Prawn Noodle  #01-15  Tue - Sun : 730am - 2.30pm
Very spacious hawker centre. Relaxed atmosphere. Be there early for black carrot cake.
Xin Heng Kee does fantastic chicken rice! Yum!
Many choices and only one stomach.
Love the prawn mee, wanton mee and especially the chee cheong fun...
Try the Pek Kio Vegetarian Bee Hoon its nice!!
Duck porridge: Did u know d stall selling kway chap #01-38 also sells very comforting $2 duck porridge? Delicious & just d right portion if u dun really hv a big appetite
Try the yam cake at the stall in the centre aisle. Full of ingredients.
Wantan mee: There are 2 wantan noodles stalls. 1 serves with black soy sauce, ala Malaysian style (#01-44); the other's (#01-04) mee kia is springier
Eat Wah Kee Big Prawn Noodles here! Very nice prawn noodles
Sin heng kee chicken n duck rice..  Super long queue.. Be prepared to wait!
Yen Heng peanut pancake is great!
Xin Heng Kee roasted meat is cheap and delicious!Starting from 2.50 :-)
iced honey lemon at the corner drinks stall (furthest from the market) is +++
Porridge: D usual stall in 1st row, facing sundry shops. There r also 2 other stalls hawkg light porridge: cooked w peanut 4 taste. 2 along the same row :-)
Sheng Seng Fried Prawn Noodles #01-40.Long wait,but worth it,
Char Siew rice here alwayz long queue!!!
Very soft n tasty
Loved the chee chong fan! Must try
Wah Kee big prawn very long queue. Either per customer order over 5 bowls or their cooking is damn slow.... Testing your patience...
Wah Kee Big Prawn Noodles at #01-15 is to die for! Beware the temperamental auntie though. Keep smiling :)
I like the fruit juice here! <3
Cheapest fried rice and hor fun in S'pore. Tong Siew at the market. $2.50.
Reasonable pricing and big portions!
Sin Heng Kee 三和一Roast Chicken, Roast Pork and Char Siew.$4.50 Use to be $3.50 =)
Pek Kio Seafood Delights #01-35, good seafood zichar and fish soup at decent prices. Fresh ingredients! Thumbs up!
Fried carrot cake: There r 2 white carrot cake stalls but clearly 1 winner: d 1 run by an old but spritely man (Good Spice #01-20) He's been dishg it out 4 @ least 20 yrs! Join d q ;-)
This stall facing the row of shops has a nice texture for their fish balls, more homemade style . Noodles were ok but their chiili, soya sauce & vinegar lacked the 'punch' 😩
pek kio seafood delight's fish soup & sheng seng fried prawn noodle 
SHENG SHENG FRIED PRAWN NOODLE ( #o1-40 )

Vegetarian options: vegetarian beehoon, you tiao (fried fritters), chee cheong fun (rice rolls), pancake, Indonesian kueh, yong tau foo, fruits, friedcarrot cake, beancurd, chwee kueh, prata, yam cake
Make this your next weekend breakfast stop. Try the amazing carrot cake, kueh chap and Wah Kee Big Prawn Noodles.
Vegetarian Mee is yummy
Nasir lemak is delicious! Their fried bee hoon is tasty, too. Love their chicken wings. Cheap & good! Thumbs up....
Fish n seafood soup next to dong ho coffee n tea is a must try with its yam rice :D
Giant prawn noodles beside charsiew stall... They've got the best tasting soup!!! Yum.
Tried Wah Kee Big Prawn Noodles after reading rave reviews. Utterly disappointing. Soup was tasteless. Stall auntie had a 'take it or leave it' attitude. Never again...
Good old school food good price
Soon Kee Wanton Mee & Opposite Economic Bee Hoon/Mee are worth mentioning for revisits again.  SK's Wanton Mee Chili is extremely spicy, extreme care needed!  Regards, Foodie Connoisseur.
通宵炒饭 food is very cheap and yummy
It's a great place if you're looking for food. It's cheap and delicious. What a perfect combination, lol.
Bean curd, porridge, chee cheong fun
Soon Kee wanton mee is fantastic, srsly. MUST TRY!!
Fried rice n char kway teow are cheap n nice n worth e price
Sample Prof Tommy Koh's faves fr this food centre: fish head soup noodle #01-46, Hokkien mee #01-40, and fried carrot cake #01-20. Source: The Sunday Times
Xin Heng Kee chicken and duck long queue.. But is nice
Sin Kee nasi lemak is one of the best I've found.
Tat Kee Noodles: Underrated! Order the stewed beef noodles! Portions are large!
I've found it! Teck Huat Coffee Loti has been relocated to BLK 341,Ang Mo Kio Avenue 1, #01-03. Famous for its Kaya bread and aromatic coffee, who once was at Pek Kio Market & Food Centre!
The prawn noodles here is not bad, but the boss abit attitude problem.
Good Spice Carrot Cake, worth the queue... $1.50 - $4.00, generous amt if eggs... :)
Having tried all the coffee stalls here, the best brew goes to Cambridge Coffee Stall (#01-06) that is facing the HDB shops.
ATM. UOB is @ convenience store next blk 45. POSB/DBS & OCBC 2 blocks away, right outside NTUC Fairprice @ Blk 43
Boon Hiang cooked Food price reasonable and wide variety of food! Must try !
Best and cheapest chicken rice store around singapore ! ♥
